Load Packages

library(RColorBrewer)
library(ComplexHeatmap)
library(multipanelfigure)

Signatures

plotTraining <- function(output.data, pathway_number, pathway){
  row_order <- order(output.data$processed.data$S_matrix[,pathway_number], decreasing = T)
  data <- output.data$processed.data$trainingData_sub[row_order,]
  prior <- output.data$processed.data$S_matrix[row_order,pathway_number]
  priorprob <- output.data$processed.data$Delta_matrix[row_order,pathway_number]
  data <- data[priorprob == 1,]
  prior <- prior[priorprob == 1]
  ha <- columnAnnotation(
    assign_pred = column_anno_barplot(
      output.data$mcmc.pos.mean.trainingData$beta_pos[,pathway_number],
      baseline = 0, bar_width=1, gp = gpar(fill = "purple")))
  colnames(data) <- gsub("_FOR_AKT", "", colnames(data))
  colnames(data) <- gsub("_18HR", "", colnames(data))
  colnames(data) <- gsub("_36HR", "", colnames(data))
  draw(rowAnnotation(
    barplotprior=row_anno_barplot(
      prior, baseline = 0, axis_direction="reverse", bar_width=1,
      gp = gpar(fill = ifelse(prior > 0, "#e6bbad", "#add8e6"),
                col = ifelse(prior > 0, "#8b0000", "#008b8b")), axis=T),
    width = unit(1.5, "cm"), gap=unit(0.1,"cm")) + 
    Heatmap(t(scale(t(data))),
            name=pathway,
            row_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = 8),
            cluster_rows = FALSE,
            cluster_columns = FALSE,
            show_row_names = FALSE,
            show_column_names = TRUE), row_title = "            Change in Expression")
}

Big Plot

figure2 <- multi_panel_figure(
  width = 13,
  columns = 4,
  height = 7,
  rows = 2,
  figure_name = "figure2",
  unit="inches")
figure2 <- fill_panel(figure2, aktplot, scaling = "shrink")
figure2 <- fill_panel(figure2, badplot, scaling = "shrink")
figure2 <- fill_panel(figure2, bimplot, scaling = "shrink")
figure2 <- fill_panel(figure2, her2plot, scaling = "shrink")
figure2 <- fill_panel(figure2, igf1rplot, scaling = "shrink")
figure2 <- fill_panel(figure2, krasplot, scaling = "shrink")
figure2 <- fill_panel(figure2, rafplot, scaling = "shrink")
figure2 <- fill_panel(figure2, snailplot, scaling = "shrink")

ggplot2::ggsave(
  "figure_signatures.pdf", figure2,
  width = figure_width(figure2, "in"),
  height = figure_height(figure2, "in"))
